Some day, students that come back and call the Pavillion at ARC, "Rec Hall", will be thought of as old fogeys.  Indeed, some of us that are Juniors and Seniors (and beyond) are already starting to feel like old fogeys with all the changes that have occured.

attachment:pavillion1.jpg  

''a view of the Pavillion at the ARC from the entrance of the ARC side''

The rec hall was a decent place to work out.  But the Powers That Be decided that it wasn't pretty and spiffy enough so they added a large extension with computer lab, stores, and all, and renamed the whole godforsaken thing the ARC.  

